'''亚历山大港的希罗'''（'''[[希腊语|希腊语]]'''：{{lang|el| ''' Ἥρων ὁ Ἀλεξανδρεύς'''}}）（{{bd|公元10年||70年|catIdx=y}}） ，是一位[[古希腊数学|古希腊数学家]]，居住于[[羅馬帝國|羅馬]]時期的[[埃及_(羅馬行省)|埃及省]]。他也是一名活跃於其家鄉[[亚历山大港|亚历山大港]]的[[工程师|工程师]]，他被认为是古代最伟大的实验家<ref name="Dictionary of Scientific Biography"> {{cite book | title=The Hutchinson dictionary of scientific biography | author = Research Machines plc. | location = 亞平頓 | publisher = Helicon Publishing | year = 2004年 | pages = 546| quote = '''Hero of Alexandria (lived c. ''AD'' 60)''' Greek mathematician and engineer, the greatest experimentalist of antiquity}}</ref>，他的著作於[[希臘化時代|希臘化時代]]科學傳統方面享負盛名。<ref>Marie Boas, "Hero's Pneumatica: A Study of Its Transmission and Influence", Isis, Vol. 40, No. 1 (Feb., 1949), p. 38 and supra</ref>

海龍發明了一種叫[[汽轉球|汽轉球]]的[[蒸汽機|蒸汽機]]。在他這麼多種發明之中，最著名的是風輪，這發明是其中一種最早利用[[風能|風能]]的設備。一般認為他也是一位[[原子論|原子論]]者，他的一些思想乃源自[[克特西比烏斯|克特西比烏斯]]（Ctesibius）的著作。

== 背景 ==
由於希羅的作品深受[[巴比倫|巴比倫]]文化的影響，所以他曾被少數[[學者|學者]]認為他是一位帶有[[古埃及|埃及]]或[[腓尼基|腓尼基]]血統的[[希臘人|希臘人]]。<ref name="Heron Egyptian">[[George_Sarton|George Sarton]] (1936年). "The Unity and Diversity of the Mediterranean World", ''Osiris'' '''2''', 第406至463頁 [第429頁] .<br />{{cite episode |title=Hero of Alexandria |series=The Engines of Our Ingenuity |serieslink=The Engines of Our Ingenuity |credits=John H. Lienhard |network=NPR |station=KUHF-FM Houston |airdate=1995年 |number=1038 |transcripturl=http://www.uh.edu/engines/epi1038.htm}}<br />T. D. De Marco (1974年). "Gas-Turbine Standby-Power Generation for Water-Treatment Plants", ''Journal American Water Works Association'' '''66''' (2), 第133至138頁.<br />Victor J. Katz (1998年). ''A History of Mathematics: An Introduction'', 第184頁. Addison Wesley. ISBN 0-321-01618-1.<br />Justin E. Wilson (2006年). [http://education.uncc.edu/cmste/summer/2006%20History%20of%20Mathematics/Justin1.doc Heron’s Formula] {{Wayback|url=http://education.uncc.edu/cmste/summer/2006%20History%20of%20Mathematics/Justin1.doc |date=20090326201121 }}, [[University_of_North_Carolina_at_Charlotte|University of North Carolina at Charlotte]].</ref>但現代學者卻認為他是一位純希臘人。<ref name="Boyer page 171-172"/><ref name="Dictionary of Scientific Biography"/><ref name="Heron Greek">{{cite book | title = A History and Philosophy of Fluid Mechanics | url = https://archive.org/details/historyphilosoph0000toka | author = Gregory A Tokaty | publisher = Courier Dover Publications | year = 1994 | isbn = 0486681033 |   pages = [https://archive.org/details/historyphilosoph0000toka/page/26 26] }}<br />{{cite book | title = Academic American Encyclopedia | url = https://archive.org/details/academicamerican0020unse | author = Grolier Incorporated | publisher = Grolier [[University_of_Michigan|University of Michigan]] | year = 1989 | isbn = 0717220249 |   pages = [https://archive.org/details/academicamerican0020unse/page/144 144] }}<br />[http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9040189/Heron-of-Alexandria/ Encyclopædia Britannica Online - Heron of Alexandria] {{Wayback|url=http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9040189/Heron-of-Alexandria/ |date=20080620003112 }}<br />{{cite book | title = Illustrated Encyclopedia of the Classical World | url = https://archive.org/details/illustratedencyc00aviy | author = Israel Shatzman, Michael Avi-Yonah | publisher = Harper and Row | year = 1975 | isbn = 0060101784 |    pages = [https://archive.org/details/illustratedencyc00aviy/page/234 234] }}<br />{{cite book | title =The Picture History of Great Inventors  | author =Gillian Clements | publisher = frances lincoln ltd | year =2005 |  isbn = 0711216053|  pages = 13 }}<br />Enc. Britannica 2007, "Heron of Alexandria"</ref>數學歷史學家[[卡爾·本雅明·博耶|卡爾·本雅明·博耶]]（C. B. Boyer）解釋，希羅之所以被認為是[[埃及|埃及人]]或[[腓尼基|腓尼基人]]，是因為他的作品帶有濃烈的巴比倫色彩。但是最少自[[阿歷山大大帝|阿歷山大大帝]]時期起至[[古典時代|古典時代]]（Classical antiquity）結束的一段時期，希臘的確與[[美索不達米亞|美索不達米亞]]有許多來往，而且不難看到巴比倫的[[算術|算術]]和[[代數|代數]][[幾何學|幾何學]]一直對希臘化文明產生重大影響。<ref name="Boyer page 171-172">{{cite book|last=Boyer|authorlink=Carl Benjamin Boyer|title=A History of Mathematics|year=1968年  [1991年] |chapter=Greek Trigonometry and Mensuration|pages=第171至172頁|quote=At least from the days of Alexander the Great to the close of the classical world, there undoubtedly was much intercommunication between Greece and Mesopotamia, and it seems to be clear that the Babylonian arithmetic and algebraic geometry continued to exert considerable influence in the Hellenistic world. This aspect of mathematics, for example, appears so strongly in Heron of Alexandria (fl. ca. A.D. 100) that Heron once was thought to be Egyptian or Phoenician rather than Greek. Now it is thought that Heron portrays a type of mathematics that had long been present in Greece but does not find a representative among the great figures - except perhaps as betrayed by Ptolemy in the ''Tetrabiblos''.}}</ref>

== 事蹟 ==
由於希羅大部份的作品（包括[[數學|數學]]、[[力學|力學]]、[[物理|物理]]和[[氣體力學|氣體力學]]）都以[[講稿|講稿]]的形式出現，所以他被認為曾在[[繆斯|繆斯]]之家教學（包括[[亞歷山大圖書館|亞歷山大圖書館]]）。此外，雖然這些[[學術|學術]]領域在[[二十世紀|二十世紀]]之前尚未正式化，但他的發明為[[模控學|模控學]]的研究資料。<ref name="Kelly">{{cite book |author=Kelly, Kevin |title=Out of control: the new biology of machines, social systems and the economic world |url=https://archive.org/details/outofcontrolnewb00kell |publisher=Addison-Wesley |location=Boston |year=1994年 |pages= |isbn=0-201-48340-8 |oclc= |doi=}}</ref>希羅發明了許多設備，例如：汽轉球、[[自動售賣機|自動售賣機]]、[[注射器|注射器]]、蒸氣風琴等。

== 發明 ==
[[File:Aeolipile_illustration.png|thumb]]
* 希羅所發明的汽轉球，是有[[文獻|文獻]]記載以來的第一部蒸汽機。它比[[工業革命|工業革命]]早二千年製造。汽轉球主要是由一個空心的球和一個裝有水的密閉[[鍋子|鍋子]]以兩個空心管子連接在一起，而在鍋底加熱使的[[水|水]]沸騰然後變成[[水蒸氣|水蒸氣]]然後由管子進入到球中，最後水蒸氣會由[[球體|球體]]的兩旁噴出並使得球體轉動。
* 世界上第一部[[自動售賣機|自動售賣機]]也是出於希羅之手，當在[[機器|機器]]頂上的槽接受了投幣者的[[硬幣|硬幣]]時，機器就會分配一定份量的聖水給投幣者。這發明被收納在希羅的書《機械學與光學》的[[列表|列表]]裡。
* 蒸氣風琴是[[歷史|歷史]]上第一部由風能推動的機器。
* 希羅發明的力泵在[[古羅馬|古羅馬]]被廣泛使用，它的其中一種用途是當作火[[引擎|引擎]]裡的其中一種零件。
* 希羅造的[[注射器|注射器]]用於傳輸[[氣體|氣體]]或[[液體|液體]]。

